verses.lines:
I will wear a crown up in heaven;
Up in heaven, up in heaven;
I will wear a crown up in heaven;
There'll be joy, such joy.

Up, up in the sky, the little birds fly;
Down, down in the nest the little birds rest;
With a wing on the left and a wing on the right,
Let the little birds sleep all the night.

The bright sun goes down, and the darkness comes on,
While the birds cease their songs;
The flowers and trees are at rest;
Praise God for His wondrous gift!

The Son, the Son, dwell in my heart;
Jesus the Son of life,
Dwell in my heart today.

If you follow Me, if you follow Me;
I will make you fishers of men,
If you follow Me.

Jesus loves the little children, all the children of the world;
He will never turn them away, He has called them all to stay,
And He cares for every child from far away.

Jesus loves the little children, all the children of the world;
Red and yellow, black and white, they are precious in His sight;
Jesus loves the little children of the world.

Millions die in lands afar, in the dark and lonely places;
They know not the love of Jesus, let us pray and let us give;
That they too may know the glory that awaits them.

Let us tell it everywhere, of the goodness of our Savior;
Let the gospel spread to all tongues, let us sing and let us shout,
Our Redeemer; and all people praise His name forever.

Give me oil in my lamp, keep me burning;
Give me oil in my lamp, I pray;
Give me oil in my lamp, keep me burning,
Keep me burning till the break of day,

Now we've come to the end, we're going home,
Goodbye, goodbye, may God keep you safe;
Goodbye, goodbye, may God watch over you.
